---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Hristijan Najcheski | Fractional SEO Consultant"
  description="The story behind why Hristijan Najcheski went fractional — and what that means for the businesses he works with today."
  schemaType="person"
>
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-header-content">
        <span class="section-label">About Me</span>
        <h1>Why I went <span class="text-gradient">fractional</span></h1>
        <p>
          Senior-level SEO expertise, embedded directly in your team — without the agency overhead or the full-time salary.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Story -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-content">
        <div class="about-text">
          <div class="about-photo">
            <img
              src="/images/author-avatar.webp"
              alt="Hristijan Najcheski — Fractional SEO Consultant"
              width="200"
              height="200"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </div>
          <h2>Hi, I'm <span class="text-gradient">Hristijan</span></h2>
          <p>
            After years working inside enterprise SEO teams and agencies, I kept seeing the same pattern: businesses were paying premium rates but getting junior account managers — not senior strategists. And the businesses that actually needed senior SEO leadership couldn't afford a full-time hire.
          </p>
          <p>
            So I went fractional. I now work with a small number of businesses at a time, embedding directly into their teams as the senior SEO lead they need — without the overhead of an agency or a full-time salary. My clients get direct access to someone who's spent 8+ years in the trenches across SaaS, e-commerce, publishing, and enterprise.
          </p>
          <p>
            My approach is simple: understand the business first, build a strategy grounded in data, and execute with the same urgency and ownership I'd apply if it were my own company. No fluff, no vanity metrics — just SEO that compounds over time and ties directly to revenue.
          </p>
          <p>
            When I'm not deep in a client's analytics or keyword data, I'm thinking about the future of search — how AI is reshaping how people find information, and how businesses can position themselves to be found in a world where the traditional blue link is no longer the only game in town.
          </p>
          <div class="about-ctas">
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Book a Free Strategy Call</a>
            <a href="/pricing/" class="btn btn-secondary">View Engagement Models →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-highlights">
          <div class="highlight-card">
            <div class="highlight-value">50+</div>
            <div class="highlight-label">Projects Completed</div>
          </div>
          <div class="highlight-card">
            <div class="highlight-value">8+</div>
            <div class="highlight-label">Years in SEO</div>
          </div>
          <div class="highlight-card">
            <div class="highlight-value">3x</div>
            <div class="highlight-label">Avg. Traffic Increase</div>
          </div>
          <div class="highlight-card">
            <div class="highlight-value">15+</div>
            <div class="highlight-label">Industries Served</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How I Work -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--color-bg-secondary);">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">How It Works</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">What working with me <span class="text-gradient">looks like</span></h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">
        A clear, repeatable process — so you always know what's happening and why.
      </p>

      <div class="approach-grid">
        <div class="approach-card">
          <div class="approach-number">01</div>
          <h3>Discovery & Audit</h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            Every engagement starts with a full audit of your business, competitors, and current SEO landscape. This isn't a template — it's a deep investigation that sets the strategic foundation.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="approach-card">
          <div class="approach-number">02</div>
          <h3>Strategy & Roadmap</h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            From the audit, I build a prioritised roadmap tied to your actual business goals. Every recommendation comes with an expected impact and effort estimate — so you know exactly what we're doing and why.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="approach-card">
          <div class="approach-number">03</div>
          <h3>Execution & Iteration</h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            I work alongside your team to implement, create content strategies, build links, and adapt in real time to algorithm updates and performance data. The strategy is always live — never static.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What I'm good at -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">Expertise</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">What I <span class="text-gradient-orange">bring to the table</span></h2>
      <div class="services-grid" style="margin-top: var(--space-10);">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Technical Mastery</h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            Site architecture, rendering, crawl optimisation, Core Web Vitals, structured data, and JavaScript SEO — the deep technical layer most consultants skip.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Content Strategy</h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            Keyword research, topic clustering, content gap analysis, and editorial strategy that drives organic traffic and moves people through the funnel.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Data & Analytics</h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            Advanced analytics setup, custom reporting, and data-driven decision-making using GA4, GSC, and enterprise tools. SEO tied to revenue, not just rankings.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">AI & GEO</h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            Generative Engine Optimisation — structuring content so AI tools like ChatGPT and Perplexity cite your business when the right questions get asked.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">Link Building</h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            White-hat link acquisition, digital PR, and authority-building strategies that hold up through algorithm updates and compound over time.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="card-title">International SEO</h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            Multi-language, multi-region SEO for businesses expanding globally — hreflang, localisation strategy, and international site architecture.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who I work with -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--color-bg-secondary);">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">Who I Work With</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">This model works best for <span class="text-gradient">specific businesses</span></h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">
        The fractional model isn't for everyone. Here's who gets the most value from it:
      </p>
      <div class="fit-grid">
        <div class="fit-card fit-yes">
          <div class="fit-label">Good fit ✓</div>
          <ul class="fit-list">
            <li>SaaS companies scaling organic acquisition</li>
            <li>E-commerce brands reducing paid dependency</li>
            <li>Publishing & media businesses growing traffic</li>
            <li>Enterprise teams needing senior SEO leadership</li>
            <li>Businesses post-migration or penalty recovery</li>
            <li>Startups that need strategy before they can hire</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="fit-card fit-no">
          <div class="fit-label">Not the right fit ✗</div>
          <ul class="fit-list">
            <li>Businesses looking for the cheapest option</li>
            <li>Companies expecting results in under 60 days</li>
            <li>Teams not willing to implement recommendations</li>
            <li>Businesses without any budget for content or tools</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .about-photo {
      width: 120px;
      height: 120px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      overflow: hidden;
      border: 3px solid var(--color-border);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    }
    .about-photo img {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
    }
    .about-ctas {
      display: flex;
      gap: var(--space-3);
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-top: var(--space-6);
    }
    .fit-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-6);
      margin-top: var(--space-10);
    }
    .fit-card {
      border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
      padding: var(--space-8);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }
    .fit-yes {
      background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.04);
      border-color: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.2);
    }
    .fit-no {
      background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.04);
      border-color: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.15);
    }
    .fit-label {
      font-family: var(--font-heading);
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: var(--text-sm);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
      color: var(--color-text-muted);
    }
    .fit-list {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--space-3);
    }
    .fit-list li {
      font-size: var(--text-base);
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
      padding-left: var(--space-5);
      position: relative;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    .fit-yes .fit-list li::before {
      content: '✓';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: var(--color-accent-blue);
      font-weight: 700;
    }
    .fit-no .fit-list li::before {
      content: '✗';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: #ef4444;
      font-weight: 700;
    }
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .fit-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .about-ctas { flex-direction: column; }
    }
  </style>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-card">
        <h2>Sound like a good fit? <span class="text-gradient">Let's talk.</span></h2>
        <p>
          A 30-minute call is all it takes to know whether and how I can help your business grow through search.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Book a Free Strategy Call →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
